---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Breadcrumb from "../components/Breadcrumb.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="For Brands — Pet Tech Visibility & Research Partnerships | SmartPetGuide"
  description="Smart pet device brands: get a free visibility snapshot showing how your product appears in search, AI citations, and owner reviews. Upgrade to a paid deep audit for actionable recommendations."
  type="article"
  publishDate="2026-06-30"
  modifiedDate="2026-06-30"
>
  <Breadcrumb crumbs={[{ label: "For Brands" }]} />

  <article>
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-forest md:text-4xl">For Pet Tech Brands</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">
      Your product is on Amazon. Owners are reviewing it. Google and AI search engines are deciding whether to show it. But do you know what they actually see?
    </p>

    <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-5 gap-y-1 text-sm text-bark-muted">
      <span>Updated: <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time></span>
      <span>4 min read</span>
    </div>

    <!-- What We Cover -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-sage-dark/30 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm md:p-8">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-forest">What We Do</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">
          SmartPetGuide is an independent research site covering <strong>smart pet devices</strong>: automatic feeders, self-cleaning litter boxes, water fountains, pet cameras, and GPS trackers. We analyze verified owner reviews, product specs, BSR and marketplace signals, comparison tables, and long-term cost data to help buyers make confident decisions.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">
          We currently cover <strong>26 products across 6 categories</strong> from brands including Litter-Robot, Petlibro, WOPET, PETKIT, Catit, eufy, Tractive, Aorkuler, CATLINK, and more. Our research reaches readers on Google, Pinterest, and AI search engines.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Problem We Solve -->
    <section class="mt-8">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-sage-dark/30 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm md:p-8">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-forest">The Visibility Problem</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">
          Most pet tech brands we've analyzed share the same blind spot: <strong>you know your product, but you don't know how it looks from the outside.</strong> What questions are buyers asking that your product page doesn't answer? Which competitor is winning the comparison articles? Are AI search engines citing accurate information about your device — or ignoring it entirely?
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">
          We built our research methodology to answer exactly these questions — for our own content. Now we offer the same analysis to brands who want to understand their visibility gaps.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How It Works: Free First Step -->
    <section class="mt-8">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-forest/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-forest/5 to-sage/20 p-6 shadow-sm md:p-8">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-forest">Start With a Free Visibility Snapshot</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">
          We'll analyze your product's current visibility across the three channels that matter most — and send you <strong>3 concrete findings</strong> you can act on today. No commitment, no pitch. Just useful data.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-sage-dark/20 bg-white p-4">
            <p class="font-semibold text-forest">Google Search</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-bark-muted">What queries bring up your product — and which ones show a competitor instead. Where your product page ranks vs where it could rank.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-sage-dark/20 bg-white p-4">
            <p class="font-semibold text-forest">AI Citation Readiness</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-bark-muted">Whether ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews can find and cite accurate information about your device — or whether they're pulling outdated or incorrect data.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-sage-dark/20 bg-white p-4">
            <p class="font-semibold text-forest">Owner Review Patterns</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-bark-muted">The 3 most common buyer objections and unanswered questions hiding in your Amazon reviews — the kind that cost you sales when buyers research before purchasing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Paid Audit Tiers -->
    <section class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-forest">Need More Depth? Pet Tech Visibility Audit</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">
        For brands ready to fix their visibility gaps, we offer a structured audit based on the same research framework we use to evaluate every product on SmartPetGuide.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        <!-- Lite -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-sage-dark/30 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-bark-muted">Lite Audit</p>
            <p class="mt-2 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-forest">$199</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-bark-muted">5-7 page report</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2.5 text-sm text-bark-muted">
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              Google visibility gaps
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              AI citation readiness check
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              Amazon owner-review pain points
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              3 quick content opportunities
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Standard -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-honey/40 bg-gradient-to-b from-honey/5 to-white p-6 shadow-md">
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-honey">Standard Audit</p>
            <p class="mt-2 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-forest">$499</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-bark-muted">12-15 page report</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2.5 text-sm text-bark-muted">
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              <strong class="text-bark">Everything in Lite</strong>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              Competitor comparison (2-3 products)
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              Buyer objection map
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              FAQ / Schema recommendations
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              30-day content roadmap
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              Optional 30-min walkthrough
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Implementation -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-sage-dark/30 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-bark-muted">Implementation</p>
            <p class="mt-2 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-forest">$1,200+</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-bark-muted">Audit + done-with-you support</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2.5 text-sm text-bark-muted">
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              <strong class="text-bark">Everything in Standard</strong>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              Content briefs (3-5 pages)
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              Comparison page copy
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              FAQ / Schema updates
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              Product positioning notes
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-honey" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              Measured distribution report
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Editorial Boundaries -->
    <section class="mt-8">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-rose-dark/20 bg-rose-light/30 p-6 shadow-sm md:p-8">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-forest">What We Don't Do</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">
          These boundaries protect both our editorial independence and your brand's credibility:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-bark-muted">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <svg class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-rose-dark/60" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-bark">We don't sell rankings.</strong> Paid work cannot change where your product appears in our editorial content. Reviews, comparisons, and Best lists remain independent.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <svg class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-rose-dark/60" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-bark">We don't guarantee positive coverage.</strong> The audit is a research product — it tells you what we find, not what you want to hear.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <svg class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-rose-dark/60" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-bark">We don't fabricate data.</strong> Every finding is sourced from public data: verified Amazon reviews, Google search results, AI engine responses, and marketplace signals.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <svg class="mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-rose-dark/60" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
            <span><strong class="text-bark">Any sponsored placement is clearly labeled.</strong> If we publish paid content in the future, it will be explicitly marked and separate from editorial rankings.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-bark-muted">
          We also welcome <strong>factual corrections</strong> — if we have a spec wrong, tell us and we'll fix it. Accurate information serves everyone.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-honey/40 bg-gradient-to-br from-honey/5 to-cream p-6 text-center shadow-sm md:p-10">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-forest">Get a Free Visibility Snapshot</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 mx-auto max-w-xl leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">
          Tell us which product you'd like us to look at. We'll send back 3 concrete, actionable findings about how your product appears to buyers researching online — at no cost and with no obligation.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6">
          <a href="mailto:press@smartpetguide.net" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-xl bg-honey px-8 py-3.5 font-bold text-white shadow-sm transition-all hover:bg-honey-dark hover:shadow-md active:scale-[0.98]">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 8l7.89 5.26a2 2 0 002.22 0L21 8M5 19h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
            press@smartpetguide.net
          </a>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-bark-muted/70">
          We typically respond within 2 business days. Your product and brand information stays confidential.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="mt-8 rounded-2xl border border-sage-dark/30 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm md:p-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-forest">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <dl class="mt-6 space-y-6">
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-forest">Who is this for?</dt>
          <dd class="mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">Pet tech brands that sell on Amazon and want to understand how their product appears in search, AI citations, and owner reviews. You don't need a marketing team — if you're the founder, this is built for you.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-forest">What do you need from me to do the audit?</dt>
          <dd class="mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">Your product name and Amazon ASIN. Everything else we need — reviews, search data, competitor positioning — is publicly available. We don't ask for your internal sales data or analytics access.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-forest">How is this different from hiring an SEO agency?</dt>
          <dd class="mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">SEO agencies optimize your website. We analyze your product's visibility across Google, AI search engines, and Amazon reviews — the places where buyers actually research before purchasing. It's a narrower, deeper analysis specific to pet tech, not a general SEO audit.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-forest">Does buying an audit get my product featured on SmartPetGuide?</dt>
          <dd class="mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-bark-muted">No. The audit is a research service, separate from our editorial content. Our reviews and recommendations remain independent. If your product is already covered on SmartPetGuide, the audit may reference that coverage but won't change it.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <p class="mt-10 border-t border-sage-dark/20 pt-4 text-xs text-bark-muted/60">
      Last updated: June 30, 2026. SmartPetGuide is an independent research site. We are not affiliated with any pet tech brand.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
